cs.CV, cs.DL, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.HC 

The paper proposes a toolkit to generate synthetic documents for training systems to perform document analysis tasks. This involves using deep learning architectures to predict the number of records for each page in handwritten structured collections. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), followed by cs.DL (Machine Learning), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), cs.LG (Machine Learning), and cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction).
